This year, the campaign will be run online, offering more than 1.9 million UAE based Emirates Skywards members a chance to join the raffle. To enter the raffle draw, customers can donate online to the Emirates Airline Foundation  – a non-profit organisation dedicated to improving the lives of children worldwide – for a chance to win big this racing season.  Winners will be announced on 28 March 2022. The raffle draw winner in third place will win 200,000 Skywards Miles; in second place, 300,000 Skywards Miles; and in first place, a grand 500,000 Skywards Miles. Emirates Skywards members and non-members can make a cash donation directly on the website using a valid credit card. To receive the prize Skywards Miles, donors must be enrolled in the Emirates Skywards programme. Winners can redeem Miles for a wide range of rewards and privileges including flights on Emirates and partner airlines, flight upgrades, hotel stays, hospitality at sporting and cultural events, and money-can’t-buy experiences. Emirates Skywards launched “Thanks a Million” in 2001, and over the past two decades, the campaign has raised more than AED 4.9 million for various charities. The Emirates Airline Foundation provides humanitarian, philanthropic aid and services for children in need across the world. The Foundation currently supports 14 projects in 9 countries – helping to improve the lives of children in need around the world regardless of geographical, political or religious boundaries. Emirates Skywards has more than 28 million members worldwide, with the fifth largest membership base in the UAE. The loyalty programme continues to provide its members with exclusive privileges, unmatched rewards and innovative  offerings. The post Emirates Skywards “Thanks a Million” is Back appeared first on TechEconomy.ng. Receive top breaking news, events, ideas, and more!